column13: Freiburg and Wolfsburg are only three points behind fourth-placed RB Leipzig in the Bundesliga, with both teams having a chance to catch up.Freiburg has impressed at Europa-Park Stadium, winning five of seven matches. Wolfsburg is in excellent form with four wins and a draw from their last five games, including convincing victories as an away side.Wolfsburg is full of confidence and we expect an open game from both teams with goals.

Empoli and Torino could have a tense low-scoring match as both teams struggle with their performances.Empoli have won just one of their seven home games, scoring two goals, while Torino have just one win in their last 11 games and have failed to score in their last three away games.Given the poor form of both teams in attack, the prediction is under 2.5 goals in the match.

Toulouse should have no trouble beating Saint Etienne, who are third from bottom of the table and have not won any of their last 14 away games in Ligue 1.The hosts recorded wins over Reims and Auxerre in their last two games on home turf. Saint Etienne lost 5-0 to Rennes in their last game as an away side and look unlikely to trouble Toulouse's defence.

Portsmouth and Derby have struggled since returning to the Championship.Portsmouth are unbeaten in their last four games but have just one away win. The return of Colby Bishop is a big plus for Portsmouth, while Derby remain vulnerable with three wins in their six home games.In seven of Portsmouth's last nine away games and five of Derby's last six at home, both teams have scored.

Valladolid and Valencia are at the bottom of La Liga, which makes this game important for both sides.Valladolid have parted ways with their coach and have yet to find form under the interim management of Alvaro Rubio.Valencia, however, have shown signs of improvement with wins in their recent games and won against Real Betis 4-2. We expect the visitors to be the better team on the pitch.

Hertha Berlin and Proyssen Munster have had a difficult season so far, with Hertha 11th in the table and Proyssen Munster among the weakest teams in the Bundesliga.Hertha have won just one of their last six games, while Proyssen Munster have two wins from 15 rounds. In their last games, both teams showed weaknesses in defense, with Hertha losing 2-1 to Greuther Fürth and Proyssen Munster falling 2-1 to Magdeburg.Hertha Berlin have scored at least one goal in 11 of their last 12 games. On the other hand, Proijsen Munster scored at least one goal in ten of the previous 12 games.

Jan Regensburg is at the bottom of the table and has a run of five games without a win, having lost all six away games this season in Bundesliga II.They have also failed to score in eight of their last ten league games.Karlsruhe is trying to recover from consecutive defeats and is in 9th place, 15 points ahead of Regensburg. Excellent opportunity to win here and gain important points.
